# Next.js App Router Conventions

## Page Structure
```
app/
  page.tsx              ← public home page
  layout.tsx            ← root layout (fonts, providers, GTM)
  admin/
    layout.tsx          ← admin shell layout
    page.tsx            ← admin index (redirects to /admin/dashboard)
    [feature]/
      page.tsx
      [slug]/page.tsx   ← dynamic detail page
  fc/
    layout.tsx
    page.tsx
    [feature]/page.tsx
  api/                  ← Next.js API route handlers
    admin/[...]/route.ts
    user/[...]/route.ts
    auth/[...]/route.ts
```

## Route Handlers (`app/api/`)
The Next.js API routes are thin proxies/middleware — keep business logic in `lib/api/routes/`. Use `NextResponse` for responses.

```ts
// app/api/admin/products/route.ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { apiRoutes } from "@/lib/api/api.route";

export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const { searchParams } = new URL(request.url);
  const page = Number(searchParams.get("page") ?? 1);
  const data = await apiRoutes.admin.product.getAllProducts({ page, ... });
  return NextResponse.json(data);
}
```

## Authentication & Middleware
- Auth state is in cookies: `token` (JWT) and `user` (JSON with `userType`)
- `middleware.ts` guards `/admin/*` and `/fc/*` — no manual auth checks needed in pages
- `userType: 1` = Admin, `userType: 2` = FC
- Supabase auth helpers live in `utils/supabase/`

## State Management in Pages
- Use **React Query** for server state (fetching, caching, mutations)
- Use **Zustand** (`store/useAuthStore.ts`) for global client state (user session, sign-up flow)
- Initialize the auth store in a `useEffect` on app load:
```ts
const { initialize } = useUserStore();
useEffect(() => { initialize(); }, []);
```

## Providers
Global providers are in `app/provider.tsx` — add new providers there (React Query, theme, etc.), not in individual layouts.

## Dynamic Routes
- Segment params are typed via `{ params: { slug: string } }` in page props
- Use `generateMetadata` for per-page SEO metadata

```tsx
// app/news/[slug]/page.tsx
export default function NewsDetailPage({ params }: { params: { slug: string } }) {
  const { slug } = params;
  // ...
}
```

## Loading & Error States
- Use Next.js `loading.tsx` for skeleton states at the route level
- Wrap async data with `<SuspenseWrapper>` from `components/wrapper/SuspenseWrapper.tsx` where needed
- Redirect to `/error` page on unrecoverable errors

## Fonts
Four CSS variables are available globally (set in `app/layout.tsx`):
- `--font-geist-sans`
- `--font-geist-mono`
- `--font-noto-sans-jp` (for Japanese text)
- `--font-cormorant-infant` (for decorative headings)
